==What is openttd.cfg?==

openttd.cfg is the configuration file which OpenTTD uses to store all its settings. This file uses the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/INI_file ini-file structure] that is a common store of configuration data in many applications. You can edit the file using any text editor.

==How does it work?==

Each time you quit OpenTTD, it writes any changes to the cfg file.
The file has all the variables organised into groups to make it easier to edit.

